node.text:
…I am forever grateful to the 43 souls who embarked on this journey with me. We arrived as strangers, but we left as family. So much healing took place—physically, emotionally, mentally, and spiritually. 💞
•
The #retreat week was filled with delicious #rawvegan meals, #fitness, #wellness classes, breath-work, meditation, fun, and so much more! It was a celebration of life and connection. ⛵️🎉✨
•
Special thank you to @jasem.ashkanani for creating this INSANE video. You really outdid yourself with this one!!! 🎥🙏🏽🎞 Thank you again to @rawchefalicia and all of the chefs and teams at @jademountainstlucia and @ansechastanet for hosting us at your resort and helping to make this event possible.
•
No future retreat dates have been set. If you’re interested in a future announcement, please sign-up for my email newsletter at www.FullyRaw.com. The link is in profile. 📲💞 For more shares and updates, please follow my @fullyrawretreats page as well. 💫
•
I can’t say or share ENOUGH about this incredible week. It was life-changing for all of us. ☀️🌈💫
•

Whether you are looking to connect with other like-minded individuals, learn about plant-based foods, or even just enjoy a healthy vacation...this retreat is a once-in-a-lifetime luxury experience. There are only 30 spots for this intimate retreat, so do not wait to book. There are less than 10 spots remaining. Please read through our website page to see all of the details, information, and itinerary. For serious inquiries, please email retreats@fullyraw.com or simply reserve your spot on the checkout page. Thank you, and I hope to be able to host you in St. Lucia for a magical retreat experience!

Those who know me, know that I love with my @pranamat. The benefits of these sets are so helpful I gifted one to all of my retreat attendees in 2019! The @pranamat is an acupressure and massage set that helps to relieve tension, reduce stress, release back pain, tone skin, and increase circulation.
•
For all my followers, I have the promo code: KRISTINA20 - it gives you 20% off everything! ✨💝✨
•
While there are so many ways to use this set, here are 5 different ways that I am showing you today...
•
1️⃣ Step on it! Give your feet a little massage. The lotus flowers touch all the pressure points on your foot, and in my opinion, this experience is better than getting a reflexology foot massage.
2️⃣ Sit on your thigh or IT band. This helps to loosen and strengthen those side leg muscles, and it also helps to tone the skin by bringing more circulation and by activating the skin and tissues.
3️⃣ Sit on it! Give your booty a little invigoration. Trust me when I say this one is intense!
4️⃣ Place the pillow under your lower-back or underneath your stomach. Stretching over the pillow is one of the best ways to release that intense lower back pain. If you're having tummy issues or simply want to help your digestion, place the pillow under your stomach and breath slowly and deeply.
5️⃣ Lay bare on your back. I recommend for beginners to use a t-shirt.
•
15-20 minutes on your set is all that it takes to experience the benefits and relief of this acupressure set. The whole set is made from the best quality sustainable hemp. It's vegan and eco-friendly and is OEKO-Tex certified.
•
20% off code: KRISTINA20
•
Enjoy my friends! 😘

node.text:
Garden update! 🌱💫 It’s a DREAM! 🥒 We just started picking our SECOND harvest of HUMONGOUS cucumbers...and my face in the second video says it all. 😂  Our organic beds are exploding with 38 different types of mixed greens, herbs, veggies, cucumbers, melons, edible flowers, and more. It’s so cool to see how much these #plants have grown. It’s LIFE. 🥬🥒✨
•
There’s truly no better feeling than getting to #grow and eat your own #food. Before dinners, Cash and I come out into the garden to pick our fresh #greens for our #salads, and we munch and munch and munch! It’s rewarding, delightful, and delicious! 🍓🍍🍊🍌✨
•
If you missed my video on how we built our organic and #sustainable #garden from beginning to end, the full video is up on my #YouTube channel (and linked in my profile). Also linked is my recommendation for #organic and #nonGMO seeds. 🎥
•
The first two beds are filled with 2 types of kale, arugula, 2 types of spinach, lettuce, tatsoi, Swiss chard, collards, beets, mustard greens, 2 types of cauliflower, broccoli, and mizuna. 🥦🥬🌱
•
The middle beds are overflowing and abundant with 4 types of cucumbers, mixed variety peppers, and hopefully soon to be watermelons. 🍅🥒🫑🌶🍉 Our tomato harvest was mostly a fail because I didn’t have the heart to move the stray cat who made a home in the tomato bed. 😭 We will soon be replanting the middle and back beds. Lots of work to come!
•
The back beds are thriving with mouth-watering and #medicinal #herbs along with beautiful edible flowers perfect to decorate any plate. 🌺🌸💫
•
No matter where you’re from or what you have access to, you can grow your own greens or sprouts in jars, on countertops, or in raised beds. I have a fun #microgreens video coming soon I can’t wait to share with you, and I hope me sharing this inspires you to start growing your own food as well. I’ll keep you posted with more updates! 🥰🙏🏽🪴 #plantpowered #vegan #gardening

node.text:
Perhaps one of the best ways to reconnect with yourself is to ALIGN with your FOOD. 🍉 We’ve all heard it before, but it’s true: YOU ARE WHAT YOU EAT. 👈🏽
•
For me, getting to sit down, crack open a juicy, ripe, local, organic, seeded watermelon, & eat as much as I want…THAT IS LIFE. It’s health freedom. 💫
•
While simplicity isn’t normally celebrated in today’s society, I find that focusing on consuming fruits and vegetables (while eliminating processed foods) not only keeps me grounded, but also brings me peace. 🌱🙏🏽🥕🥦🥬🥒☀️
•
There’s something to be said about taking the TIME to rest, nourish, nurture, love, and be PRESENT. If you’re feeling unsettled or overwhelmed right now, try something new.
•
The most magical shifts occur when we take the time to enjoy, heal, and be present with ourselves. 🌺
•
📸 @cashgotwings 
#fullyraw #vegan #watermelon #summer #local #organic #plantbased #youarewhatyoueat

node.text:
16 YEARS RAW VEGAN TODAY! 🥳🎉🌺🥑🍉✨ I went from being a hyperglycemic, type 2 diabetic 18-year old to a strong, healthy woman…and I’ve never looked back. To say that it’s been 16 years since I’ve consumed meat, dairy, gluten, processed foods, etc. is a bit mind-blowing. 🤯 Still here I am standing, in the best health & shape of my life. This journey has changed me and given me life, and I’m forever grateful. 🙏🏽✨
✨
 I look back and only imagine what my life would be like without this GIFT of knowledge and health freedom. ✨🎁 ✨ While it hasn’t been an overnight transformation, every growth opportunity I’ve encountered has shaped who’ve I am today. 🥭 For those who say that diet or lifestyle choices doesn’t matter, I’m a living testimony THAT THEY DO. Eating plant-based with a rich emphasis on more fruits and vegetables helps you to feel your best, and importantly, helps save animal lives and the planet too. 🐛🌎🦋💕
✨
I’ve learned so much the past 16 years, and what I’ll share with you is this: keep moving forward. Every step you take matters. Start with one #fullyraw #vegan meal a day. Plan. Prepare. Share. Learn to grow your own food and live sustainable. Life compassionately. This is an abundant lifestyle! 🥥 And while it may seem like it’s all about the food...it’s about much more than that—it’s body, mind, and spirit healing. 🌸 To those who’ve been on this journey with me and who have continued to support and encourage me...I love you. THANK YOU! Here’s to another 16 years to come!!! 🥭🍇🍓🥑🍊🍒🍉✨
✨
📸 @cashgotwings
✨
Big announcement coming tomorrow! Be sure to keep watch of my website at www.FullyRaw.com 🍉
✨

node.text:
Something I’ve learned about myself is this: I AM FULLY CAPABLE OF MY OWN HEALING. 🐛🦋💫
•
Understanding my inner workings has forced me to be even MORE UBER conscious of my own self-talk. If it’s not with LOVE, it cannot happen. 🌸 Love is the most powerful healing FORCE of all.
•
I don’t need to call my friends every time something hurts—I do better by first going WITHIN and time to process my emotions. I have the key within myself. 🔑
•
Another thing I’ve learned: sharing too much with your friends without asking is highly inappropriate. It shows a lack of boundaries for their space…and for yours. I’m on my journey to learning better boundaries with myself and with others. 🌊
•
I’ve come to realize we all have the answers within us. 🔑🔑🔑 If we just take a few moments to listen to our intuition & to pay attention to how we are truly feeling, shifts can take place and miracles can happen. 🙏🏽
•
This mentality also gives us permission to take full responsibility over our own emotions, pains, changes, relationships, healing, and more. 🌿
•
We are capable of our own healing. No one else can do it for you. When in doubt go within…the answers are there waiting for you. 🙏🏽🔑💫
•
Wishing you all a peaceful, graceful, and loving weekend. 💗
•
